 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>O ye al whilk that<note type="tnote-indicator" n="1">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="1">G</note> by me cummes and gothe,<note type="enote-indicator" n="1">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="2">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="1">who</gloss><gloss n="2"> come and go</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Attende and behold this warldes vanyté.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="3">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="3">world’s vanity</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>To lyke symylitude,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="4">G</note> be ye lefe or lothe,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="5">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="4">alike appearance</gloss><gloss n="5"> loving or loathing</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Sal<note type="gloss-indicator" n="6">G</note> ye cum<note type="gloss-indicator" n="7">G</note> for al your warldly<note type="gloss-indicator" n="8">G</note> prosperité.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="6">Shall</gloss><gloss n="7"> come</gloss><gloss n="8"> worldly</gloss></l><l><milestone n="5" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Thinne<note type="gloss-indicator" n="9">G</note> abydyng here is in no stabilité:<note type="gloss-indicator" n="10">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="9">Thine</gloss><gloss n="10"> permanence</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Yowthe sal<note type="gloss-indicator" n="11">G</note> passe and his verteus swage<note type="gloss-indicator" n="12">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="11">shall</gloss><gloss n="12"> diminish</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/><persName>Deth</persName> sal cum and lyfe sal hafe<note type="gloss-indicator" n="13">G</note> passage.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="13">have</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Why art thou so sett in prowde elacyon,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="14">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="14">arrogance</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And with the desyres of worldly covetyse?<note type="gloss-indicator" n="15">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="15">covetousness</gloss></l><l><milestone n="10" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Why in wrathe has thou syche distrubacoun<note type="gloss-indicator" n="16">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="16">disturbance</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>With invyos<note type="gloss-indicator" n="17">G</note> swellyng of gret malyce?<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="17">envious</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Glotony<note type="gloss-indicator" n="18">G</note> usyng wher les wald<note type="gloss-indicator" n="19">G</note> suffyce?<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="18">Gluttonous</gloss><gloss n="19"> less would</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Brynnyng in slomer<note type="gloss-indicator" n="20">G</note> and slawly in corayge,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="21">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="20">Burning in slumber</gloss><gloss n="21"> slothful in desire</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Or to be lycheros<note type="gloss-indicator" n="22">G</note> for al syche life has sone<note type="gloss-indicator" n="23">G</note> pasayge.<note type="enote-indicator" n="2">N</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="22">lecherous</gloss><gloss n="23"> soon</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><milestone n="15" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Thogh gleteryng<note type="gloss-indicator" n="24">G</note> thou be as byrnysched<note type="gloss-indicator" n="25">G</note> gold bright,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="24">glittering</gloss><gloss n="25"> burnished</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>None to thee lyke thee semes in lusty purtrature.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="26">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="26">handsome form</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Ilk<note type="gloss-indicator" n="27">G</note> men byn stowte<note type="gloss-indicator" n="28">G</note> in his<note type="gloss-indicator" n="29">G</note> perfyte right,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="27">These</gloss><gloss n="28"> bold</gloss><gloss n="29"> their</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Enformed<note type="gloss-indicator" n="30">G</note> with bewtes<note type="gloss-indicator" n="31">G</note> by nature,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="30">Developed</gloss><gloss n="31"> beauties</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And with strenth<note type="gloss-indicator" n="32">G</note> also to fortefye thi<note type="gloss-indicator" n="33">G</note> fygure.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="32">strength</gloss><gloss n="33"> their</gloss></l><l><milestone n="20" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>The day sal cum<note type="gloss-indicator" n="34">G</note> thou sal out of this warld wende<note type="gloss-indicator" n="35">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="34">shall come</gloss><gloss n="35"> go</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Thi mortal fayte of thee sal make ane ende.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="36">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="36">an end</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Wher is <persName>Salomon</persName><note type="gloss-indicator" n="37">G</note> now with al his prudence,<note type="enote-indicator" n="3">N</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="37">Solomon</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Or myghty <persName>Sampson</persName>, duk<note type="gloss-indicator" n="38">G</note> invyncybyll,<note type="enote-indicator" n="4">N</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="38">Sampson, duke</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/><persName>Tullyus</persName><note type="gloss-indicator" n="39">G</note> the retrysciane<note type="gloss-indicator" n="40">G</note> with al his eloquence,<note type="enote-indicator" n="5">N</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="39">Cicero</gloss><gloss n="40"> rhetorician</gloss></l><l><milestone n="25" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Or <persName>Arystotil</persName><note type="enote-indicator" n="6">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="41">G</note> in witt moste sensybyll,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="41">Aristotle</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Or this emprour <persName>Octavy</persName><note type="gloss-indicator" n="42">G</note> mest pessybyll,<note type="enote-indicator" n="7">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="43">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="42">Octavian</gloss><gloss n="43"> most peaceable</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Or swete <persName>Jonathas</persName><note type="gloss-indicator" n="44">G</note> ful amyabyll.<note type="enote-indicator" n="8">N</note> <note type="enote-indicator" n="9">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="45">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="44">Jonathan</gloss><gloss n="45"> amiable</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Wher bene<note type="gloss-indicator" n="46">G</note> thies clerkes so experte in clergy,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="47">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="46">are</gloss><gloss n="47"> learned doctrine</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Thies kynges and prynce myghty and stronge</l><l><milestone n="30" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Al ar thai gone and close<note type="gloss-indicator" n="48">G</note> with twynkillyng of ane ee.<note type="enote-indicator" n="10">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="49">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="48">buried</gloss><gloss n="49"> an eye</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Of this warldly<note type="gloss-indicator" n="50">G</note> joy the feste dures<note type="gloss-indicator" n="51">G</note> not longe.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="50">worldly</gloss><gloss n="51"> feast endures</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>That joy is endyd as a schadow<note type="gloss-indicator" n="52">G</note> us emonge.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="53">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="52">shadow</gloss><gloss n="53"> among</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Here is no lastyng ese<note type="gloss-indicator" n="54">G</note> ne no tranquyllité<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="54">ease</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Bot labour, travell,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="55">G</note> and myche adversyté.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="55">travail</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><milestone n="35" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Remembyr thi selfe — here is no sykyr abydynge,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="56">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="56">secure dwelling</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And se how this warld is so transitory.</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Thou must departe, here is no long dwellynge</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>As <persName>Job</persName> says in his funerall obsequye,<note type="enote-indicator" n="11">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="57">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="57">sad funeral rites</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>In whos servyse thou may lerne to dye,<note target="#1" type="footnotelink">1</note></l><l><milestone n="40" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Whos tretys<note type="gloss-indicator" n="58">G</note> is a perfyte<note type="gloss-indicator" n="59">G</note> evydence<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="58">treatise (book)</gloss><gloss n="59"> complete</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>To schew what sal be after thine existence.</l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>O erthly man, why rejoyces thou thee of gudes erthly,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="60">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="60">earthly possessions</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Sen<note type="gloss-indicator" n="61">G</note> erthe sal to erth,<note type="enote-indicator" n="12">N</note>  what is thi cause?<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="61">Since</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Remembyr thi selfe on ilk<note type="gloss-indicator" n="62">G</note> syde verely.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="63">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="62">each</gloss><gloss n="63"> truly</gloss></l><l><milestone n="45" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>No chartyr may help, byll scrow, ne clawse,<note target="#2" type="footnotelink">2</note></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Thine abydyng here is bot a lytel pawse<note type="gloss-indicator" n="64">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="64">pause</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>It vanysches away and that hastely<note type="gloss-indicator" n="65">G</note><space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="65">quickly</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>As<note type="tnote-indicator" n="2">T</note>  teches experience dayly.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="66">G</note><space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="66">experience teaches [us] daily</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>We that wer sum tyme in this wardles passayge<note type="gloss-indicator" n="67">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="67">world’s passage</gloss></l><l><milestone n="50" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>War<note type="gloss-indicator" n="68">G</note> myghty strong and replete in ryches<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="68">Were</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Into powdyr<note type="gloss-indicator" n="69">G</note> we sal fall,<note type="enote-indicator" n="13">N</note>  be we nover<note type="tnote-indicator" n="3">T</note>  so sayge,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="70">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="69">powder</gloss><gloss n="70"> never so wise</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Of wardly joy syche<note type="gloss-indicator" n="71">G</note> is the progresse.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="71">such</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>O barayne saule<note type="gloss-indicator" n="72">G</note> that is so witles,<space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="72">barren soul</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>That in the lyfes space cannot remembyr</l><l><milestone n="55" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Thi selfe, safe<note type="gloss-indicator" n="73">G</note> that sal be dust ilk membyr.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="74">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="73">except</gloss><gloss n="74"> every limb</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Why is thi hert so sett in gladnes?</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>For to wormes mete<note type="gloss-indicator" n="75">G</note> thou art grathed<note type="gloss-indicator" n="76">G</note> and made,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="75">worms’ food</gloss><gloss n="76"> prepared</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>For erth is gifen<note type="gloss-indicator" n="77">G</note> to erth in sothfastnes,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="78">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="77">given</gloss><gloss n="78"> in truth</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>The flesche is borne into dethe to be hade.</l><l><milestone n="60" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>O wretchyd man, whi art thou so glad,</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>With syche daliaunce<note type="gloss-indicator" n="79">G</note> and fals elacoun?<note type="gloss-indicator" n="80">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="79">dalliance</gloss><gloss n="80"> arrogance</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Why wantes<note type="gloss-indicator" n="81">G</note> thou reson and discrecoun?<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="81">lack</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Man, remembyr of the dawnce of makabre,<note type="enote-indicator" n="14">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="82">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="82">Dance of Macabre</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>How lordes spritual and also temperall,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="83">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="83">spiritual and earthly lords</gloss></l><l><milestone n="65" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Yowthe nor age ther has none lyberté,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="84">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="84">freedom</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Bot must passe be <persName>Dethes</persName> dedes mercyall.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="85">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="85">by Death’s merciful deeds</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Wherfore lat<note type="gloss-indicator" n="86">G</note> it be oft in thi memoriall,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="87">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="86">let</gloss><gloss n="87"> memory</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>For the tyme sal aproche hence for to wende<note type="gloss-indicator" n="88">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="88">to go</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And to a lyke semblande<note type="gloss-indicator" n="89">G</note> be broght to ende.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="89">semblance</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><milestone n="70" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>When <persName>Deth</persName> sal smyte<note type="gloss-indicator" n="90">G</note> thee with his mercyal<note type="gloss-indicator" n="91">G</note> darte,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="90">strike (smite)</gloss><gloss n="91"> merciful</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>By paynes strong throghe thi hert rote,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="92">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="92">heart’s root</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Mynysteryng<note type="gloss-indicator" n="93">G</note> the poyntes<note type="gloss-indicator" n="94">G</note> of his sore<note type="gloss-indicator" n="95">G</note> arte,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="93">Administering</gloss><gloss n="94"> activities</gloss><gloss n="95"> painful</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>No help ne socour than nedes to mote.<note target="#3" type="footnotelink">3</note></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Resembyl this fygure, ther is none other bote<note type="gloss-indicator" n="96">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="96">remedy</gloss></l><l><milestone n="75" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>And thi reward hafe,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="97">G</note> owther<note type="gloss-indicator" n="98">G</note> gode or yll,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="97">have</gloss><gloss n="98"> either</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>When the tyme cummes <foreign xml:lang="lat">ite venite</foreign><note type="enote-indicator" n="15">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="99">G</note> to fulfyll.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="99">come and go</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Who sum ever it be that by this cummes and gothe,</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Stande and behold this litterall scripture<note type="enote-indicator" n="16">N</note> </l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And it se and over rede, be thou lefe or lothe,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="100">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="100">willing or unwilling</gloss></l><l><milestone n="80" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Thi wepyng teres fast sched in gode ure.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="101">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="101">good fortune</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Thou art now as I was in warldly fygure;<note type="gloss-indicator" n="102">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="102">worldly form</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>I was as thou art, sum tyme be<note type="gloss-indicator" n="103">G</note> dayes olde.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="103">by</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>O pray ye al for me, I pray<note type="gloss-indicator" n="104">G</note> yow a thowsand-folde.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="104">ask</gloss></l></lg>
 
 </div><div type="footnotes">
 
